$ Excel Object Model: Application.DisplayAlerts

The boolean value of `application.displayAlerts` controls whether Excel prompts the user for a response using a message box or just assumes the action's default value.

This value is typically set to `false` when executing → development/languages/VBA macros that should run through without user interaction.
-
A typical situation where the user interaction might be desired to be prevented is
  • the `saveAs()` metho of the `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook` object.
  • the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet/delete[`delete`] method of the `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet` object

sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Object-Model/Application#ms-object-model-application-displayAlerts[`displayAlerts`] as → Microsoft/Office/Object-Model/Application[common property in other Office `application` objects].

  Other → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application#excel-application-display-properties[`display*` properties]
  of the `→ Microsoft/Office/Object-Model/Application` object.
